applyMatrix4

  • applyMatrix4(σ: Matrix4): Vector3
    • Defined in davinci-eight/math/Vector3.ts:195

    Pre-multiplies the column vector corresponding to this vector by the matrix. The result is applied to this vector. Strictly speaking, this method does not make much sense because the dimensions of the square matrix and column vector don't match. TODO: Used by TubeSimplexGeometry.

    method

    applyMatrix4

    chainable

    Parameters

    • σ: Matrix4

      The 4x4 matrix that pre-multiplies this column vector.

    Returns Vector3

Static dual

  • dual(B: BivectorE3, changeSign?: boolean): Vector3
    • Defined in davinci-eight/math/Vector3.ts:756

    Constructs a vector which is the dual of the supplied bivector, B. The convention used is dual(m) = I * m. If a sign change is desired from this convention, set changeSign to true.

    Parameters

    • B: BivectorE3
    • Default value changeSign: boolean = false

    Returns Vector3
